This course delves into the pivotal role of finance in shaping environmental sustainability. It provides a comprehensive exploration of green financing and investment products, highlighting their distinctions from conventional financial products and addressing the associated issues and challenges in their creation and utilization. The course also tackles the concern of greenwashing within the financial context. Throughout the program, Estonian financial practitioners make significant contributions by sharing their practical experience in developing green financial solutions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to familiarize participants with the main concepts, trends, and challenges in the field of Green Finance through the prism of green financial products.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, participants will:  - understand the significance of sustainability and the primary sustainability challenges in financial decision-making;  - establish a connection between climate change science and finance; - acquire knowledge of key terms, metrics, and financial instruments related to sustainability; - gain insights into the barriers to green finance and the challenges of transforming conventional financial products and services into environmentally-friendly ones; - recognize the issue of greenwashing in finance.
